abstract: President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
snippet: President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
headline_main: Trump Slams 'Unfair' Pelosi Delay, Rallies Conservatives
headline_print_headline: Trump Slams 'Unfair' Pelosi Delay, Rallies Conservatives

abstract: New Williams scored a season-high 24 points with six 3-pointers, Nate Grimes added 12 points and Fresno State beat IUPUI 95-64 on Friday night after holding the Jaguars to 25 first-half points.
snippet: New Williams scored a season-high 24 points with six 3-pointers, Nate Grimes added 12 points and Fresno State beat IUPUI 95-64 on Friday night after holding the Jaguars to 25 first-half points.
lead_paragraph: FRESNO, Calif. — New Williams scored a season-high 24 points with six 3-pointers, Nate Grimes added 12 points and Fresno State beat IUPUI 95-64 on Friday night after holding the Jaguars to 25 first-half points.
headline_main: Williams Scores 24 Points, Fresno State Downs IUPUI 95-64
headline_print_headline: Williams Scores 24 Points, Fresno State Downs IUPUI 95-64

abstract: More than 1,500 protesters have been arrested across India in the past 10 days, officials said, as police try to quell  sometimes violent demonstrations against a citizenship law that critics say undermines the country's secular constitution.
snippet: More than 1,500 protesters have been arrested across India in the past 10 days, officials said, as police try to quell  sometimes violent demonstrations against a citizenship law that critics say undermines the country's secular constitution.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI/MUMBAI — More than 1,500 protesters have been arrested across India in the past 10 days, officials said, as police try to quell sometimes violent demonstrations against a citizenship law that critics say undermines the country's secular constitution.
headline_main: Hundreds Arrested in India During Days of Protests Over Citizenship Law
headline_print_headline: Hundreds Arrested in India During Days of Protests Over Citizenship Law

abstract: The California winemakers  who hosted a dinner at a “wine cave” for Democratic presidential hopeful Pete Buttigieg are defending the fundraising event.

lead_paragraph: The Department of Homeland Security’s Office of Inspector General said Friday that it had found “no misconduct or malfeasance” by department officials in the deaths of two Guatemalan children who died in the custody of the United States Border Patrol last year.

headline_main: Their Meeting Was Music to Her Ears

abstract: The couple were introduced by a Manhattan family court referee in 2015. The groom was assigned to serve as the bride’s court-appointed lawyer.
snippet: The couple were introduced by a Manhattan family court referee in 2015. The groom was assigned to serve as the bride’s court-appointed lawyer.
lead_paragraph: Kristin Maria Cahill and James Ernest Iñiguez were married Dec. 21 at the Atelier Ballroom in Jersey City, N.J. Jaimee Lynn Nelson, a Universal Life minister and a friend of the couple, officiated.
